1
00:00:14,567 --> 00:00:15,800
<i> Why did he send this to me?</i>

2
00:00:17,667 --> 00:00:18,733
<i> Hey.</i>

3
00:00:21,300 --> 00:00:22,500
<i>Is that it?
Have you got it?</i>

4
00:00:22,633 --> 00:00:23,767
<i>What do you even need that for?</i>

5
00:00:24,200 --> 00:00:25,133
<i> You don't have to know.</i>

6
00:00:27,567 --> 00:00:29,833
<i> Help! Help!</i>

7
00:00:29,967 --> 00:00:31,500
<i> Joel?</i>

8
00:00:31,633 --> 00:00:33,200
<i> Joel!</i>

9
00:00:33,333 --> 00:00:34,633
<i>- What happened?
- Please help Joel.</i>

10
00:00:34,800 --> 00:00:36,733
<i> I'm begging you, please!</i>

11
00:00:36,867 --> 00:00:38,900
<i>- Alice, please!
- Start CPR.</i>

12
00:00:44,300 --> 00:00:45,533
<i> Why did you stop?</i>

13
00:00:45,667 --> 00:00:47,167
<i> There's no use.</i>

14
00:00:47,300 --> 00:00:48,233
<i> I'm sorry.</i>

15
00:00:48,367 --> 00:00:50,100
<i> Time of death, 5:03.</i>

16
00:00:50,233 --> 00:00:52,200
<i>- No! No!
- Andrea...</i>

17
00:00:53,367 --> 00:00:54,867
<i> Joel!</i>

18
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:57,033
<i> Joel!</i>

19
00:00:57,167 --> 00:00:59,133
<i>Killing someone isn't
part of our plan.</i>

20
00:00:59,267 --> 00:01:00,333
<i> Just me?</i>

21
00:01:00,467 --> 00:01:02,900
<i>Both of us,
you're already in this.</i>

22
00:01:03,033 --> 00:01:06,000
<i> Dad, Joel's gone.</i>

23
00:01:06,133 --> 00:01:09,433
<i> My best friend is gone, Dad.</i>

24
00:01:09,600 --> 00:01:10,667
<i> I'm sorry, Joel.</i>

25
00:01:10,800 --> 00:01:12,667
<i>I didn't mean for this
to happen to you.</i>

26
00:01:12,800 --> 00:01:14,800
<i>But all of you better
be ready...</i>

27
00:01:14,933 --> 00:01:16,800
<i> because I'm not stopping.</i>

28
00:01:16,933 --> 00:01:20,000
<i>Thank you, Andrea, for
everything you did for Joel.</i>

29
00:01:20,133 --> 00:01:23,867
<i>Thank you, everyone,
for accepting our brother.</i>

30
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:28,367
<i>Thank you
for sharing him with us.</i>

31
00:01:28,500 --> 00:01:29,833
<i> It's really sad, Andrea.</i>

32
00:01:29,967 --> 00:01:31,333
<i>You were the only one he ever
took seriously.</i>

33
00:01:31,467 --> 00:01:32,933
<i> If you'd said yes back then,</i>

34
00:01:33,067 --> 00:01:34,467
<i>maybe it would've
led to marriage.</i>

35
00:01:34,600 --> 00:01:36,500
<i> Whoever did this to Joel...</i>

36
00:01:36,633 --> 00:01:38,467
<i> whoever killed him...</i>

37
00:01:38,600 --> 00:01:40,467
<i> I hope they're caught soon.</i>

38
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:44,100
<i>And I hope they rot
in jail for life.</i>

39
00:01:48,133 --> 00:01:49,867
Okay, one more.

40
00:01:52,533 --> 00:01:53,967
Oh, oh, oh...

41
00:01:54,100 --> 00:01:55,933
- It hurts a bit.
- Okay, one more, Sir.

42
00:01:56,067 --> 00:01:59,433
Yes, maybe it's sore,
we were standing for so long

43
00:01:59,567 --> 00:02:00,600
at the funeral.

44
00:02:01,633 --> 00:02:03,267
So Joel's been laid
to rest, Sir.

45
00:02:04,467 --> 00:02:06,333
How's the investigation?

46
00:02:06,467 --> 00:02:10,433
Was it confirmed
that it was really an overdose?

47
00:02:10,567 --> 00:02:11,633
Not yet.

48
00:02:12,667 --> 00:02:15,600
There's a possible case
of foul play.

49
00:02:17,833 --> 00:02:21,333
You know what?
I can't get it off my mind.

50
00:02:21,467 --> 00:02:23,467
Was what happened to Joel
just a coincidence?

51
00:02:24,500 --> 00:02:27,167
Just recently,
Coleen almost got hurt.

52
00:02:27,767 --> 00:02:30,767
And then Andrea,
and now, it's Joel.

53
00:02:31,833 --> 00:02:34,033
Maybe it's just
a coincidence, Sir.

54
00:02:34,167 --> 00:02:37,067
Coleen and Andrea's attackers
are different people.

55
00:02:37,200 --> 00:02:38,300
No.

56
00:02:38,433 --> 00:02:40,500
It's possible that only
one person ordered

57
00:02:40,633 --> 00:02:42,833
and paid them to do it.

58
00:02:42,967 --> 00:02:45,200
Who would even do that?

59
00:02:45,333 --> 00:02:46,500
My wife.

60
00:02:47,633 --> 00:02:48,900
She hates us so much,

61
00:02:49,033 --> 00:02:50,800
especially Felma.

62
00:02:50,933 --> 00:02:52,367
I'm sure of it.

63
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:56,000
She had something to do with
what happened

64
00:02:56,133 --> 00:02:56,933
to Andrea and Coleen.

65
00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:00,233
But I can't see
any connection...

66
00:03:01,367 --> 00:03:03,467
to what happened
to Joel because...

67
00:03:03,833 --> 00:03:05,200
he didn't do Hazel
anything wrong.

68
00:03:05,333 --> 00:03:06,267
Oh?

69
00:03:06,400 --> 00:03:08,767
Why would that woman target him?

70
00:03:28,133 --> 00:03:29,567
<i> I'm really sorry.</i>

71
00:03:30,867 --> 00:03:32,933
<i> Miss, I'm sorry.</i>

72
00:03:36,267 --> 00:03:38,567
<i>Call me if you need someone
to talk to.</i>

73
00:03:38,700 --> 00:03:40,300
<i>Let's go to a coffee shop,
I'm willing to listen.</i>

74
00:03:43,200 --> 00:03:45,433
<i>What's the good news?
You even brought a cake.</i>

75
00:03:46,967 --> 00:03:49,267
<i>You got the virtual
assistant job? Yes!</i>

76
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:51,400
<i>- Congrats!
- Thank you!</i>

77
00:03:53,233 --> 00:03:55,233
<i>How dare you try to hurt Andrea!</i>

78
00:03:55,400 --> 00:03:56,933
<i> Joel!</i>

79
00:03:57,967 --> 00:03:59,200
<i> Joel! Joel, that's enough.</i>

80
00:03:59,333 --> 00:04:00,567
<i> Stop.</i>

81
00:04:18,067 --> 00:04:19,400
I'm sorry, Joel.

82
00:04:21,367 --> 00:04:23,267
I didn't realize sooner...

83
00:04:24,700 --> 00:04:26,467
that you matter to me.

84
00:04:27,833 --> 00:04:32,333
I didn't realize right away
how much you valued me.

85
00:04:34,200 --> 00:04:35,700
But I realize it now.

86
00:04:37,567 --> 00:04:40,033
I wish I had told you
I love you.

87
00:04:44,100 --> 00:04:45,567
I love you, Joel.

88
00:04:48,900 --> 00:04:50,633
And I will always love you.

89
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:10,367
Sis.

90
00:05:10,500 --> 00:05:13,100
Sis, it's time to eat.

91
00:05:13,233 --> 00:05:15,233
I brought you your favorite.

92
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:27,733
Sis, you're not okay.

93
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:35,267
You know, Coleen...

94
00:05:39,533 --> 00:05:43,933
When I saw how he protected me

95
00:05:44,067 --> 00:05:45,800
from those perverts...

96
00:05:48,500 --> 00:05:55,400
I could clearly see
how worried he was.

97
00:05:57,300 --> 00:05:58,933
How he valued me.

98
00:05:59,933 --> 00:06:03,133
I was really planning
to accept his feelings.

99
00:06:04,567 --> 00:06:07,367
I was just waiting
for the anniversary

100
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:09,267
of our first meeting.

101
00:06:10,800 --> 00:06:12,067
But it won't.

102
00:06:12,200 --> 00:06:13,633
That won't happen anymore.

103
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:19,633
If only we had been given
the chance

104
00:06:19,767 --> 00:06:22,967
to make more memories together.

105
00:06:25,267 --> 00:06:27,700
But we could't do
all that anymore.

106
00:06:29,433 --> 00:06:32,367
Andrea, remember?

107
00:06:33,533 --> 00:06:36,933
I felt the same
when Jessica died.

108
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:40,333
If we'd made up sooner...

109
00:06:42,667 --> 00:06:46,000
I would've had so many more
happy memories with her.

110
00:06:47,300 --> 00:06:49,233
But that didn't happen.

111
00:06:52,700 --> 00:06:54,700
But Timo is already in jail.

112
00:06:55,600 --> 00:06:58,433
Jessica's death has already been
given justice.

113
00:07:01,900 --> 00:07:03,067
But Joel...

114
00:07:04,767 --> 00:07:09,300
What happened to Joel
deserves justice.

115
00:07:12,067 --> 00:07:14,667
He deserves justice,
he deserves it, too.

116
00:07:31,767 --> 00:07:33,233
This is what we'll do,
Ma'am Felma.

117
00:07:33,367 --> 00:07:36,167
Just straighten your fingers.

118
00:07:36,300 --> 00:07:37,467
Then, let's imagine

119
00:07:37,600 --> 00:07:40,300
there's a ball
in your right hand.

120
00:07:40,433 --> 00:07:43,233
So, there,
just press them together.

121
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:45,300
There.

122
00:07:45,433 --> 00:07:49,067
Then the other one, slowly.

123
00:07:49,233 --> 00:07:50,767
There, one more.

124
00:07:50,900 --> 00:07:52,233
Mom...

125
00:07:53,567 --> 00:07:56,267
Andrea's still lonely.

126
00:07:56,400 --> 00:07:57,833
She's still crying.

127
00:07:59,933 --> 00:08:02,000
Don't worry, sweetie.

128
00:08:02,133 --> 00:08:04,767
We'll sleep by her side tonight.

129
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:08,000
Yes, Felma.

130
00:08:08,133 --> 00:08:09,933
We'll sleep by Andeng's side.

131
00:08:10,067 --> 00:08:11,600
Can I join, too?

132
00:08:12,667 --> 00:08:14,800
I remember when...

133
00:08:14,933 --> 00:08:17,000
Dad felt lonely,

134
00:08:17,133 --> 00:08:20,267
Jessica and I would sleep
by his side.

135
00:08:20,400 --> 00:08:22,367
Do you still remember that, Dad?

136
00:08:22,533 --> 00:08:23,533
Of course, sweetie.

137
00:08:24,833 --> 00:08:27,333
I could really fee
how much you loved me.

138
00:08:28,100 --> 00:08:30,900
So we'll do the same
with your older sister.

139
00:08:31,833 --> 00:08:33,567
We'll comfort her as a family.

140
00:08:33,700 --> 00:08:35,967
So that she'll feel
a little less lonely.

141
00:08:38,367 --> 00:08:41,733
<i>When they found out Jessica
wasn't their real sister,</i>

142
00:08:41,867 --> 00:08:42,833
<i> they hurt her...</i>

143
00:08:43,900 --> 00:08:45,700
<i> abused her...</i>

144
00:08:45,833 --> 00:08:48,000
<i> and mistreated her.</i>

145
00:08:48,133 --> 00:08:50,533
<i> Until the child got depressed.</i>

146
00:08:50,667 --> 00:08:52,533
<i> Until our daughter died.</i>

147
00:08:55,433 --> 00:08:57,667
Ma'am Felma, let's continue.

148
00:08:57,800 --> 00:08:59,100
Come on.

149
00:09:01,600 --> 00:09:02,833
There.

150
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:06,367
Then, let's just do it
from the start.

151
00:09:07,633 --> 00:09:09,200
That's okay.

152
00:09:09,333 --> 00:09:10,467
There.

153
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:14,967
I heard from Colonel Sarabia

154
00:09:15,100 --> 00:09:17,733
that autopsy was done
on Joel's remains.

155
00:09:19,233 --> 00:09:20,700
His cause of death...

156
00:09:23,167 --> 00:09:24,800
respiratory depression...

157
00:09:25,567 --> 00:09:28,100
leading to injuries
to the brain.

158
00:09:30,300 --> 00:09:33,967
His brain lost
its oxygen supply.

159
00:09:34,100 --> 00:09:36,167
The syringe...

160
00:09:37,067 --> 00:09:38,933
what about the drug that was
injected into him?

161
00:09:41,133 --> 00:09:42,367
Well...

162
00:09:43,667 --> 00:09:45,267
he was given a toxic dose.

163
00:09:46,567 --> 00:09:50,167
It was that drug that shut down
his breathing.

164
00:09:51,167 --> 00:09:52,433
My god.

165
00:09:52,567 --> 00:09:56,267
They also checked the vial
and syringe used

166
00:09:56,400 --> 00:09:57,633
for fingerprints.

167
00:09:58,133 --> 00:10:01,467
But only Joel's
fingerprints were found.

168
00:10:02,667 --> 00:10:06,067
That means he was the only one
who held that syringe and drug.

169
00:10:07,900 --> 00:10:10,633
- Which probably means that...
- That's impossible.

170
00:10:10,767 --> 00:10:11,733
No.

171
00:10:12,767 --> 00:10:14,700
Joel couldn't do that
to himself.

172
00:10:15,467 --> 00:10:17,033
He couldn't...

173
00:10:17,167 --> 00:10:18,567
He couldn't do that.

174
00:10:18,700 --> 00:10:21,533
He was not
that kind of person, Mom.

175
00:10:21,667 --> 00:10:23,967
He could never do that.

176
00:10:26,033 --> 00:10:27,700
He wasn't like that.

177
00:10:40,567 --> 00:10:43,167
How fingerprints end up
on surfaces?

178
00:10:45,167 --> 00:10:47,200
When a person touches a surface,

179
00:10:47,333 --> 00:10:50,267
they usually leave sweat, oil,

180
00:10:50,400 --> 00:10:54,567
and fatty acids from the skin
and other contaminants.

181
00:10:54,700 --> 00:10:59,700
These residue create latent
fingerprints.

182
00:11:11,200 --> 00:11:13,067
Dad, dad, look at this.

183
00:11:14,200 --> 00:11:15,200
I forgot about this.

184
00:11:15,333 --> 00:11:16,700
But I've seen it now.

185
00:11:17,967 --> 00:11:19,500
This is the video Joel
sent to me

186
00:11:19,633 --> 00:11:21,167
before he went to the restroom.

187
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:25,833
Hazel was at the hospital
that day.

188
00:11:26,867 --> 00:11:28,800
Could she have something to do
with what happened to Joel?

189
00:11:37,333 --> 00:11:38,667
Sir, that the woman
in the video...

190
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:42,433
we suspect her in Joel's death.

191
00:11:43,767 --> 00:11:45,567
She's been banned
from that hospital.

192
00:11:45,700 --> 00:11:46,767
But she was still there.

193
00:11:46,900 --> 00:11:48,267
She still went there.

194
00:11:51,567 --> 00:11:52,900
Who was she talking to?

195
00:11:55,433 --> 00:11:57,067
Sir, it was too far.

196
00:11:57,200 --> 00:11:58,833
I couldn't recognize him.

197
00:11:58,967 --> 00:12:00,100
But I'm sure he's Hazel's man.

198
00:12:00,233 --> 00:12:02,167
She hired him to kill Joel.

199
00:12:03,133 --> 00:12:04,100
He's right.

200
00:12:07,133 --> 00:12:10,467
Mr. Cruz, there's nothing
incriminating in this video.

201
00:12:10,867 --> 00:12:12,833
Just because you have
a video recording

202
00:12:12,967 --> 00:12:16,600
doesn't prove she's the killer
or she ordered the murder.

203
00:12:16,767 --> 00:12:19,033
Hazel has a long history
of what she's done to us.

204
00:12:19,167 --> 00:12:22,167
She hired men to mess
with our family.

205
00:12:23,333 --> 00:12:24,633
I'm sure that

206
00:12:24,767 --> 00:12:26,800
whoever that man
in the video is,

207
00:12:26,933 --> 00:12:29,433
he's the one Hazel hired
to kill Joel.

208
00:12:30,400 --> 00:12:31,900
What's the motive then?

209
00:12:37,433 --> 00:12:41,700
Sir, why would Joel send
that video to me

210
00:12:41,833 --> 00:12:43,700
if it wasn't important?

211
00:12:43,833 --> 00:12:46,700
I'm sure he wanted
to tell me something.

212
00:12:46,833 --> 00:12:48,700
But he couldn't do it,
he never got the chance

213
00:12:48,867 --> 00:12:50,367
because he was killed!

214
00:12:52,333 --> 00:12:56,867
Sir, Ma'am,
we can't accuse anyone

215
00:12:57,000 --> 00:12:59,433
based on speculation.

216
00:12:59,567 --> 00:13:01,700
I'm sorry, but we need

217
00:13:01,833 --> 00:13:05,633
strong evidenc
to support your claim.

218
00:13:07,833 --> 00:13:11,033
There's another way
to know the truth.

219
00:13:17,033 --> 00:13:18,000
Hazel!

220
00:13:20,400 --> 00:13:20,733
Open the gate!

221
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:22,200
Hazel!

222
00:13:23,333 --> 00:13:24,367
- Hazel!
- Wait!

223
00:13:24,500 --> 00:13:25,967
- What's going on?
- Get out of there!

224
00:13:27,167 --> 00:13:29,033
I said wait! I'm coming!

225
00:13:31,833 --> 00:13:33,167
What are you doing here?

226
00:13:33,300 --> 00:13:34,867
You killed Joel, didn't you?

227
00:13:36,033 --> 00:13:37,500
Joel? Who's Joel?

228
00:13:37,633 --> 00:13:39,233
Stop denying it.

229
00:13:39,367 --> 00:13:40,433
Alice was there.

230
00:13:40,567 --> 00:13:42,100
It's impossible that she didn't
mention it to you.

231
00:13:42,233 --> 00:13:45,767
She was on duty when Joel
was rushed to the ER.

232
00:13:45,900 --> 00:13:47,600
I don't know
what you're talking about.

233
00:13:49,267 --> 00:13:52,633
Joel, you're lover.

234
00:13:52,767 --> 00:13:54,367
What do I care about him?

235
00:13:54,500 --> 00:13:55,800
Why would I do that?

236
00:13:55,967 --> 00:13:56,833
Please.

237
00:13:56,967 --> 00:13:57,900
I'm not a killer.

238
00:13:58,033 --> 00:13:59,400
Be careful with your
accusations.

239
00:13:59,533 --> 00:14:01,233
You're such a liar!

240
00:14:01,367 --> 00:14:02,900
You were at the hospital
that day!

241
00:14:03,033 --> 00:14:04,067
Joel saw you!

242
00:14:05,133 --> 00:14:06,167
What the...

243
00:14:08,067 --> 00:14:09,067
Here.

244
00:14:10,933 --> 00:14:12,100
We have evidence.

245
00:14:13,267 --> 00:14:15,800
Joel sent this to me
before he died.

246
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:28,567
Alice.

247
00:14:33,400 --> 00:14:34,367
Are you okay?

248
00:14:39,200 --> 00:14:41,700
I can't sleep well, Jojo.

249
00:14:42,933 --> 00:14:47,767
I feel guilty since it happened.

250
00:14:49,900 --> 00:14:52,867
I gave Hazel the stuff
she used for...

251
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:54,800
Let's not talk about it.

252
00:14:58,567 --> 00:14:59,867
How about you?

253
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:01,200
Are you okay?

254
00:15:02,867 --> 00:15:06,267
Why would he send this video
without a reason?

255
00:15:07,700 --> 00:15:08,833
I don't know.

256
00:15:10,300 --> 00:15:12,567
Shouldn't I get mad instead?

257
00:15:12,700 --> 00:15:15,667
He was recording me
without my consent.

258
00:15:15,800 --> 00:15:18,767
He wouldn't sent that video
if it wasn't important.

259
00:15:19,933 --> 00:15:22,100
Who was the man
you were talking to?

260
00:15:22,233 --> 00:15:24,933
Did you hire him to inject
the drug into Joel?

261
00:15:26,033 --> 00:15:27,467
Or maybe you did it.

262
00:15:27,600 --> 00:15:29,967
You're a nurse.
You know how to do it.

263
00:15:30,100 --> 00:15:33,100
They didn't get your
fingerprints on the syringe

264
00:15:33,233 --> 00:15:34,533
because you put gloves on.

265
00:15:34,700 --> 00:15:37,200
What now?
Admit it, Hazel!

266
00:15:37,333 --> 00:15:38,867
Wow, that's impressive.

267
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:41,033
You're good at making up
stories.

268
00:15:42,333 --> 00:15:44,133
Hazel, we're not fooling
with you.

269
00:15:44,267 --> 00:15:45,600
Who was the man
you were talking to?

270
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:48,400
Wait.

271
00:15:48,533 --> 00:15:49,533
Why?

272
00:15:49,667 --> 00:15:51,600
Why should I tell you?

273
00:15:51,733 --> 00:15:54,567
Should I report to you everyone
I talk to?

274
00:15:55,733 --> 00:15:57,933
After leaving me
for your mistress?

275
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:03,167
Besides, I was at the hospital
to see Alice.

276
00:16:03,300 --> 00:16:04,933
But I bumped into that man.

277
00:16:05,067 --> 00:16:07,900
Fine, for your satisfaction,
I'll tell you.

278
00:16:08,067 --> 00:16:09,733
I don't know him.

279
00:16:09,867 --> 00:16:12,133
He's a random stranger asking

280
00:16:12,267 --> 00:16:14,667
for directions to the
department.

281
00:16:14,800 --> 00:16:17,233
So I told him where to go.
That's all.

282
00:16:18,667 --> 00:16:23,500
And why would I waste time
on Joel?

283
00:16:23,633 --> 00:16:25,567
Who is he?

284
00:16:25,700 --> 00:16:27,267
He doesn't matter to me.

285
00:16:28,767 --> 00:16:30,500
What now?

286
00:16:30,633 --> 00:16:32,300
Cat got your tongue?

287
00:16:33,633 --> 00:16:35,933
Is there anything else
you'd like to say?

288
00:16:36,067 --> 00:16:37,567
Because you're wasting my time.

289
00:16:37,700 --> 00:16:39,033
Leave if you have nothing else
to say.

290
00:16:40,167 --> 00:16:41,200
Is that all?

291
00:16:42,367 --> 00:16:43,433
Leave.

292
00:16:57,033 --> 00:16:57,967
What?

293
00:16:58,100 --> 00:16:59,500
We were caught on video?

294
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:05,200
But don't worry,
they didn't recognize you.

295
00:17:05,333 --> 00:17:08,733
You had your back to Joel
when the footage was taken.

296
00:17:08,867 --> 00:17:11,667
What if they're doing something
now to identify me?

297
00:17:12,833 --> 00:17:14,800
Hazel, our time might be
running out.

298
00:17:14,967 --> 00:17:16,833
Maybe we should stop.

299
00:17:18,467 --> 00:17:21,000
What about the justice
for Jessica?

300
00:17:21,133 --> 00:17:23,733
Jojo, you once rejected
our daughter.

301
00:17:25,033 --> 00:17:27,233
You left her when she wasn't
even born yet.

302
00:17:29,533 --> 00:17:35,500
And now even until death you'll
leave her behind?

303
00:17:53,500 --> 00:17:58,100
Do you really think Hazel
would confess?

304
00:18:00,167 --> 00:18:04,733
We had a hard time
getting her to admit

305
00:18:04,867 --> 00:18:06,833
to the other things she did.

306
00:18:06,967 --> 00:18:08,867
Do you really think
she'd confess to this?

307
00:18:11,467 --> 00:18:15,033
Murder is a serious crime.

308
00:18:15,167 --> 00:18:18,867
But could that guy
be Hazel's boyfriend?

309
00:18:20,067 --> 00:18:21,067
Right?

310
00:18:22,133 --> 00:18:23,100
It's a shame

311
00:18:23,233 --> 00:18:27,033
we can't tell whether
he's good-looking or not.

312
00:18:27,167 --> 00:18:28,400
Didang, stop.

313
00:18:30,200 --> 00:18:31,833
I just have a strong gut feeling

314
00:18:33,067 --> 00:18:36,300
that the video has something to
do with what happened to Joel.

315
00:18:36,433 --> 00:18:40,633
If only we could identify
that man.

316
00:18:40,767 --> 00:18:45,400
I'm sure he's involved
in what Hazel did to Joel.

317
00:18:45,533 --> 00:18:49,967
When did Joel see Hazel?

318
00:18:52,867 --> 00:18:56,600
He told me he was just going
to use the restroom.

319
00:18:57,833 --> 00:19:01,367
And he told me to wait
in the car.

320
00:19:01,500 --> 00:19:03,533
I did.

321
00:19:03,667 --> 00:19:07,000
But he took forever.

322
00:19:08,067 --> 00:19:10,533
Then he sent me that video.

323
00:19:12,133 --> 00:19:15,800
At first, I ignored it because
I was trying to call him.

324
00:19:15,933 --> 00:19:17,100
So...

325
00:19:17,233 --> 00:19:21,567
between the time I was waiting
and when I went back inside,

326
00:19:23,067 --> 00:19:26,467
that's probably when Joel
saw Hazel and that man.

327
00:19:29,733 --> 00:19:38,000
The crime happened
during this timeframe?

328
00:19:41,433 --> 00:19:45,233
We really need to know who
that man is.

329
00:19:45,367 --> 00:19:49,633
I'm sure he's the only one
who can tell us the truth.

330
00:20:00,400 --> 00:20:03,533
I feel for Andrea, Manuel.

331
00:20:04,933 --> 00:20:10,833
It's already hard grieving
someone you love,

332
00:20:11,967 --> 00:20:13,867
and now

333
00:20:14,000 --> 00:20:15,767
she can't even find peace

334
00:20:15,900 --> 00:20:19,800
because she doesn't know
what really happened.

335
00:20:20,867 --> 00:20:24,033
No. I believe Hazel is involved
in what happened.

336
00:20:24,167 --> 00:20:27,000
Even what happened to Andrea
and Coleen.

337
00:20:27,133 --> 00:20:29,700
There's no way it was just
a coincidence.

338
00:20:31,167 --> 00:20:32,167
Ouch.

339
00:20:32,300 --> 00:20:35,233
Sorry.

340
00:20:36,767 --> 00:20:40,767
Does she want to hurt us?
Is that what this is, Dad?

341
00:20:42,867 --> 00:20:44,767
Looks like it, dear.

342
00:20:46,100 --> 00:20:48,100
What I don't get is...

343
00:20:49,233 --> 00:20:53,067
why was Joel dragged into this?

344
00:20:54,200 --> 00:20:56,667
Is she seeking revenge?

345
00:20:57,833 --> 00:21:02,433
She still can't accept that
Coleen had nothing to do

346
00:21:02,567 --> 00:21:05,200
with what happened to Jessica?

347
00:21:05,333 --> 00:21:06,933
Yes, it's possible.

348
00:21:09,067 --> 00:21:10,500
If that's the case,

349
00:21:11,800 --> 00:21:14,667
our eldest isn't safe.

350
00:21:31,833 --> 00:21:32,867
Ready.

351
00:21:34,000 --> 00:21:35,200
There it is.

352
00:21:35,333 --> 00:21:36,233
Hi!

353
00:21:36,367 --> 00:21:37,600
Hi, Aunt Coleen!

354
00:21:37,733 --> 00:21:39,800
Hello, Jeff.

355
00:21:39,933 --> 00:21:42,233
Son, I'm glad you called.

356
00:21:42,400 --> 00:21:44,000
<i> We were worried about you.</i>

357
00:21:44,133 --> 00:21:47,033
Mom, Dad, sorry.
I got busy with my family.

358
00:21:47,167 --> 00:21:50,100
And there's so much to see here.
We've been going around.

359
00:21:50,233 --> 00:21:51,367
That's okay.

360
00:21:51,500 --> 00:21:54,000
What matters is you're safe.

361
00:21:54,133 --> 00:21:56,333
Hi, Pretty Mama!
Hi, Handsome Papa!

362
00:21:56,467 --> 00:21:58,567
Hi, Tetay!

363
00:21:58,700 --> 00:21:59,867
Hi, sweetie!

364
00:22:00,000 --> 00:22:02,767
Princess, how are you?

365
00:22:02,900 --> 00:22:04,033
I'm happy.

366
00:22:04,167 --> 00:22:06,967
Jesus heard our prayers.

367
00:22:07,100 --> 00:22:08,700
You're better now.

368
00:22:08,833 --> 00:22:10,300
<i> That's true.</i>

369
00:22:10,433 --> 00:22:13,067
You pray so well.

370
00:22:15,200 --> 00:22:18,600
Jo, come eat with us.
Go on, sit here.

371
00:22:18,767 --> 00:22:20,833
Sure, sir. Thank you.

372
00:22:20,967 --> 00:22:23,033
<i> Jojo's there. Jo, hey.</i>

373
00:22:24,333 --> 00:22:27,267
Your dad and I
are doing therapy.

374
00:22:29,200 --> 00:22:31,333
Daisy, how are you?

375
00:22:31,467 --> 00:22:33,233
I'm okay, Auntie.

376
00:22:34,633 --> 00:22:37,167
I'm sorry about what
happened before.

377
00:22:37,300 --> 00:22:39,567
Tetay and I left suddenly.

378
00:22:39,700 --> 00:22:43,500
We didn't get to say goodbye
properly.

379
00:22:43,633 --> 00:22:45,067
That's okay.

380
00:22:45,200 --> 00:22:47,900
Forget about it.

381
00:22:48,033 --> 00:22:49,100
Where's Andrea?

382
00:22:52,567 --> 00:22:54,867
She's in her room, resting.

383
00:22:55,000 --> 00:22:57,100
Please. I know her.

384
00:22:57,233 --> 00:22:58,800
She's probably just texting
Joel.

385
00:22:58,933 --> 00:23:01,833
You know that girl?
She's such a pretender.

386
00:23:01,967 --> 00:23:04,867
It's obvious she's in love
with Joel, too.

387
00:23:05,000 --> 00:23:06,100
Jeff...

388
00:23:07,367 --> 00:23:09,400
Joel's gone.

389
00:23:10,867 --> 00:23:12,200
What do you mean by gone?

390
00:23:21,300 --> 00:23:23,233
I can't be here enjoying myself

391
00:23:23,400 --> 00:23:24,300
while you're dealing
with all this.

392
00:23:24,433 --> 00:23:25,333
I'm coming home.

393
00:23:25,467 --> 00:23:28,033
I'll find evidence
to put that woman in jail.

394
00:23:28,167 --> 00:23:29,133
Any news?

395
00:23:29,267 --> 00:23:31,467
Aside from them suspecting you,

396
00:23:31,600 --> 00:23:34,833
Jeffrey already knows
what happened to Joel.

397
00:23:34,967 --> 00:23:36,200
That's it?

398
00:23:36,333 --> 00:23:38,233
What are you planning to do?

399
00:23:38,367 --> 00:23:39,533
Kill him, too?

400
00:23:41,133 --> 00:23:42,300
<i> Hazel!</i>

401
00:23:42,433 --> 00:23:44,733
<i> Come out here! Hey!</i>

402
00:23:44,867 --> 00:23:46,633
Colonel Sarabia has an update.

403
00:23:46,767 --> 00:23:48,633
They've ruled out suicide.

404
00:23:48,767 --> 00:23:51,133
As they should, Uncle.
Joel wasn't a drug user.

405
00:23:51,400 --> 00:23:53,600
He was murdered.
Hazel killed him.
